text:
King's Highway, at the S.W. corner of Ave. J., showing the Mayflower Hospital. Also seen is 4006-4012 Ave. J., south side, west from King's Highway.

August 7, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH
title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue J

text:
Kings Highway, north from Avenue J, showing a W. P. A. highway project. The thoroughfare bends eastward at Avenue I (white sign). Views 2 and 3 show Kings Highway at Avenue I and East 45th Street, the row of two-story dwellings being on the latter; view 3 is south from East 46th Street.

Views 1,2: Sept. 25, 1935
Views 3,4: Oct. 21, 1935
